stylometry: We are consindering using Chipotle Company for our project. We are considering using the problem "How many burritos, chicken, steak, barbaqoa, carnitas will be needed to be sold in order to break even? Now each buritto will have its own fix cost and variable cost becuase the price to make each burrito will be different. We will most likely be looking at a quarter or three months becuase that is when chipotle shares its balance statements. The management problem is that are we incurring more costs than profit. Each burrito contains a certain amount of variable and fix costs and at times those costs cost Chipotle more than it profits them. Aggregate planning objective is to minimize the amount of a variable to be able to cover a set amount of nodes. Aggregate planning can choose the best solution to minimze costs yet at the same time be able to cover set of criteria. Such as how many doctors are needed in order to cover a nite shift at the hospital. We can use aggregate planning to figure out the optimal solution for that. It creates the best or optimal schedule for a particular situation. The trade off is that if your using the least amount of resources to cover a schedule are you producing the best results. If five doctors are capable of covering a nite shift but eight doctors would be the best number doctors, the trade of is, is you can have 5 doctors run the shift, have less costs, but are the patients being best attended for? Or you can incurr the costs of having 8 doctors cover the shift and have all the patients better provided for. That is the trade off.
